GLOBAL GIFT FOUNDATION ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS

   For more than a decade, Maria Bravo has received recognition for her
   national and international philanthropic career, both in her name and
   in that of her foundation.

WE ARE ONE GALA 2017

   Michel Issa, founder of one of the most important philanthropic galas
   in Europe, the “We Are One Gala”, handed Maria Bravo an award at the We
   Are One Gala, in recognition of her philanthropic work through the
   Foundation.

   The award was presented to Maria during the gala celebration at the
   Friends Arena in Stockholm, Sweden on the 31st January. The delivery
   was accompanied by a surprise video of the actress and activist Eva
   Longoria, where the actress praised the work of Maria as Founder and
   CEO of Global Gift Foundation.

     *
     *
     *
     *
     *
     *

   IFRAME: https://www.youtube.com/embed/h9zdkD9W2N8?feature=oembed

III CORAZÓN SOLIDARIO AWARDS 2016

   Global Gift Foundation received an award from Corazon magazine on
   behalf of jewellry brand Folli Follie. Every year, several NGO´s
   receive a donation for their dedication and help to society.

   Five foundations were recognized for their different achievements –
   Child Welfare, Third World, Animal Welfare, Woman Rights and Social
   Action which was awarded to Global Gift Foundation.

     *
     *
     *
     *
     *
     *

SOLIDARITY AWARD – COPE Network 2015

   The COPE radio network awards Maria Bravo with their Cofrade Solidarity
   Award.

     *
     *
     *

Recognition of the President of One2one MK & Events 2014

   Councilor for Tourism of the City of Marbella, José Luís Hernández and
   the president of the One2one MK & Events company, give María Bravo the
   yearly award dedicated to philanthropy in recognition of The Global
   Gift Gala as Best Event of the Year.

     *

The Children For Peace ONLUS awards Maria Bravo for her Philanthropic work

   The Children for Peace gave María Bravo of the Global Gift Foundation
   an award in recognition of her years of tireless work and diligence
   benefiting non-profit organizations, as well as men, women and children
   in need. For her humility, gentility, vision and her extraordinary
   efforts making her more than worthy of this recognition.

   2014

     *
     *
     *

Recognition from City Council of Marbella

   The City Council of Marbella and Mayor, Mª Ángeles Muñoz, acknowledged
   Maria Bravo´s philanthropic trajectory exercised the last few years
   both on a national and international level during the celebration of
   The Global Gift Gala, Marbella 2014. The Mayor gave a commemorative
   plaque on behalf of the whole city and showed her personal gratitude.

   2014

     *
     *

Recognition of Sportsmen for a Cause to María Bravo

   2014

     *
     *
     *

Recognition of the Marbella City Council

   The Mayor of Marbella, Mª Ángeles Muñoz, awarded María the “2013
   Solidarity Prize”:

   “In recognizing Maria Bravo for her altruistic and disinterested work
   in favor of our city and its most disadvantaged people.”

   2013

     *

Marbella Volunteer Platform Award

   The Marbella Volunteer Platform Award gave Maria their most significant
   award – the Silver Pin. The award was handed over by the Mayoress
   during the annual celebration of “Marbella Crea”.

     *
     *
     *
     *
     *

Recognition of the Mayor of Los Angeles, USA

   Mr Antonio R. Villaraigosa, Mayor of the City of Los Angeles,
   recognizes in his name and on behalf of the residents of Los Angeles
   Maria´s achievements over the years.

   “As Mayor of the City of Los Angeles and on behalf of its residents, it
   is a pleasure to congratulate you for your recognition by the One
   Children’s Foundation celebrating its 4th anniversary. Your commitment
   and dedication to the city of Los Angeles is indeed commendable. On
   this special occasion, I am pleased to join with members of the
   community in recognizing your achievements and accomplishments over the
   years”.

     *

Recognition of Los Angeles County Councilor District 13, USA

    “To Maria Bravo, with sincere thanks for her outstanding philanthropic
   work with the Eva Longoria Foundation and the ONE Foundation. His
   dedication improves the lives of others in the City of Los Angeles”.

     *

